{
  "texts": [
    "However, when algorithms are designed to generate new instructions based on input data, systems can detect patterns, begin to \"learn,\" and update its behavior accordingly.",
    "Such self-improving systems are AI, and they approximate human-level capabilities.",
    "AI became feasible due to exponential increases in computing power, the availability of large datasets, and the development of sophisticated algorithms (Olson, 2024; Rheinberger, 2023; Whittaker, 2021).",
    "Machine Learning (ML) is a subset of AI that, by examining labeled data, develops a model that fits the data.",
    "These models take various forms."
  ]
}